<ns2815:section xmlns:ns2815="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.security.introduction.securityContextPropagation">

  <ns2816:title xmlns:ns2816="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Security Context Propagation</ns2816:title>
  <ns2817:para xmlns:ns2817="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Enterprise beans (e.g. session beans) invoked by a client may themselves call further
    enterprise beans (session beans or entity beans). The security context -- the caller
    role(s) and principals -- is automatically propagated between the beans.
  </ns2817:para>
</ns2815:section>